        <mxCell id="note" value="💡  A team for tricky jobs, too — when grading a long assignment, the AI uses a small team of specialists that hand work to each other (one analyses the submission, another decides the grade). This can run on a custom-built engine or on a popular ready-made AI toolkit (CrewAI) — an admin can switch between them at any time." style="shape=note;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;backgroundOutline=1;fillColor=#ECE9F3;strokeColor=#7A6B98;fontSize=13;fontColor=#3D4A5C;align=left;spacingLeft=14;spacingTop=10" vertex="1" parent="1">
          <mxGeometry x="130" y="690" width="1630" height="64" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>

        <mxCell id="footer" value="Why it matters:  a team working in parallel means the AI Companion answers in a couple of seconds, not half a minute." style="text;html=1;align=center;whiteSpace=wrap;fontSize=14;fontStyle=2;fontColor=#1F3A68" vertex="1" parent="1">
